#C Street of replicators pushes blinker 5 units west and 3 units north
#C in 246 gens. In this push the blinker ends up on a different
#C diagonal, but a second, parallel street can then push it 3 units west
#C and 5 units north, for a net push of 8 units northwest.  The streets are
#C far enough apart so that they won't interfere with each other.
#C Dean Hickerson, 1999
